        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusLedger",
            fallback = "Santa checks names. Krampus checks balances. The ledger under {{stashNoun}} had pages for cowardice, cruelty, mercy, theft, and one page labeled survival in handwriting that kept changing.\n\nI do not know where {{openerName}} lands. The notes on {{entryNameA}} and {{entryNameB}} are free enough to use, but if the page asks what you did at the roadblock, lie badly.",
            professionGroups = {"combat", "medical", "stealth"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusChimneyAsh",
            fallback = "The chimney ash spelled names after midnight. Not every name belonged to the living, and not every living name stayed in one place. {{authorName}} swept it twice before the broom started bleeding soot.\n\nThe gift for {{openerName}} is {{entryNameA}} and {{entryNameB}}, wrapped before the ash could correct them. If the fireplace coughs, do not answer in your own voice.",
            professionGroups = {"stealth", "trades", "medical"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusFrozenCreek",
            fallback = "Krampus crossed the frozen creek without leaving footprints. The convoy did not. We found boots, rifles, candy wrappers, and one package tied with ribbon under {{stashNoun}}.\n\n{{openerName}} can keep {{skillName}} and {{entryNameB}}. The creek keeps the rest. Do not test the ice if it sounds like bells.",
            professionGroups = {"outdoors", "combat", "fitness"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusDepartmentStore",
            fallback = "The department store Santa was gone, but the chair kept asking children what they wanted. Adults sat in it too after the food ran out. Nobody liked the answers.\n\n{{survivorName}} found this journal in the gift wrap aisle. I added {{entryNameA}} beside a roll of red paper and {{entryNameB}} beside the tape. If {{openerName}} sees the chair, keep walking.",
            professionGroups = {"food", "stealth", "trades"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusSleighTracks",
            fallback = "The tracks behind the school were too narrow for a truck and too deep for a deer. They circled the playground seven times, then stopped at the quarantine notice like something had paused to read.\n\nInside the package were {{entryNameA}}, {{entryNameB}}, and a smell like old snow. {{openerName}} should use the first two and ignore the smell if it starts giving advice.",
            professionGroups = {"outdoors", "medical", "stealth"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusCandleFactory",
            fallback = "The candle factory kept working after everyone left. Wax poured, wicks twisted, and every label printed the same warning: good enough is not good. {{authorName}} stole three candles and came back with four shadows.\n\nThis journal was inside the fourth. {{skillName}} is legible. {{recipeName}} smells faintly of smoke. If {{openerName}} lights anything from that place, do it outdoors.",
            professionGroups = {"trades", "stealth", "food"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusSnowman",
            fallback = "The snowman outside city hall had coal eyes, twig arms, and teeth that were not coal. Every morning it faced a different house. Every night one more window went dark.\n\n{{authorName}} hid {{entryNameA}} in the scarf and {{entryNameB}} under the hat. {{openerName}} can take the notes, but leave the teeth. Gifts should not bite back.",
            professionGroups = {"stealth", "combat", "medical"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusConfessionBox",
            fallback = "Krampus does not need confession, but he enjoys bookkeeping. The box behind {{noun}} was full of apology notes, ration tickets, and a single gift tag with {{openerName}} already written on it.\n\n{{entryNameA}} is what the tag offered. {{entryNameB}} is what {{authorName}} added in defiance. Keep both, but do not apologize to the box.",
            professionGroups = {"medical", "stealth", "combat"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusMilkCookies",
            fallback = "Milk spoiled. Cookies molded. The plate stayed full anyway. Something took one bite every night and left a small black hoofprint in the crumbs.\n\n{{survivorName}} said it meant we were chosen. I said chosen for what. The answer was this journal, {{entryNameA}}, {{entryNameB}}, and a ribbon tied too tight to untangle.",
            professionGroups = {"food", "medical"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusMadLibsRibbon",
            fallback = "The ribbon went {{adverb}} around {{adjective}} {{noun}} while {{omenNoun}} {{verb}} behind {{stashNoun}}. Krampus wrote {{openerName}} on the tag in {{supplyNoun}} and smiled with somebody else's teeth.\n\nOpen {{entryNameA}} first, {{entryNameB}} second, and say {{exclamation}} only if the bells start counting.",
            professionGroups = {"stealth", "outdoors", "combat"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusMadLibsList",
            fallback = "The list said {{adjective}} {{noun}}, {{dangerNoun}}, and {{supplyNoun}} were naughty. It said {{authorName}} was pending. It said {{openerName}} would understand when {{omenNoun}} {{verb}} {{adverb}}.\n\nThe useful parts are {{skillName}}, {{entryNameB}}, and whatever courage survives {{exclamation}}.",
            professionGroups = {"combat", "medical", "fitness"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusSkillOnlyBundle",
            fallback = "The bundle had no candy, no coal, and no apology. Only {{skillNameA}} folded around {{skillNameB}}, tied with string that felt warm through gloves.\n\n{{openerName}} should learn both before nightfall. Krampus gives warnings in the shape of gifts because people open gifts faster.",
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusSkillOnlyBell",
            fallback = "Every bell meant practice. One ring for {{skillNameA}}, two rings for {{skillNameB}}, three rings for running before the lesson becomes personal.\n\n{{authorName}} made it to two. {{openerName}} should not wait for three.",
            professionGroups = {"fitness", "stealth", "combat"},
        },
        {
            key = "UI_BurdJournals_LoreTemplate_KrampusSkillOnlyCoalDust",
            fallback = "{{skillNameA}} was written in coal dust across the first page. {{skillNameB}} appeared when the dust was wiped away. The table underneath stayed clean.\n\nThat is not a miracle. It is a warning with tidy hands. {{openerName}} should take the knowledge and leave the dust.",
            professionGroups = {"trades", "medical"},
        },
        {
